# {{ project_name }}

> {{ project_description }}

Generated from [OpenProductKit](https://github.com/youruser/openproductkit) — a white-label product-template built around **one decoupled core** with thin web / CLI adapters.

## Architecture

```
packages/core        Pure Python domain models + Repository ports. No FastAPI, no DB, no HTTP.
apps/backend         FastAPI adapter. Owns SQLModel persistence (implements core ports).
apps/cli             Typer CLI + task runner ({{ cli_name }}).
apps/frontend        React + Vite web UI. Talks to the backend over HTTP.
```

Business logic lives only in `packages/core`. Everything else is a delivery mechanism.

## Develop

```bash
uv sync --dev                 # install the Python workspace
uv run {{ cli_name }} hello         # smoke test
uv run {{ cli_name }} doctor        # check your toolchain
uv run {{ cli_name }} dev           # API + a basic web page on http://127.0.0.1:8000

# Rich web UI (separate terminal):
pnpm install
pnpm -C apps/frontend dev     # http://127.0.0.1:5173 (proxies /api to the backend)
```

## Test & lint

```bash
uv run {{ cli_name }} test          # pytest across the workspace
uv run {{ cli_name }} lint          # ruff
```

## Keep up to date with the template

```bash
copier update                 # pull upstream OpenProductKit improvements
```
